### Natural History

The land that became Mather Air Force Base is home to rare wetland [vernal pools](/Vernal_pool), a unique ecological feature of California. The site supports a diverse array of plant and animal species, primarily within a grassland ecosystem. This community continues to harbor a significant number of native grasses and [forb](/Forb) species. Among the notable native wildflowers found here is the [Yellow Mariposa Lily](/Calochortus_luteus). Another significant species is the [Vernal Pool Buttercup](/Ranunculus_bonariensis) var. trisepalus. The vernal pools themselves provide critical habitat for species such as [Ahart's Dwarf Rush](/Juncus_leiospermus) var. ahartii, [Boggs Lake hedgehyssop](/Gratiola_heterosepala), and the rare [Legenere limosa](/Legenere_limosa).

